<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 8:16PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Craig, Ottawa and
east central Nowata Counties through 845 PM CDT...
At 816 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from near Welch to 12 miles east of Lenapah. Movement
was northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Miami...                          Vinita...
Baxter Springs...                 Commerce...
Fairland...                       Afton...
Quapaw...                         Welch...
Bluejacket...                     Treece...
Picher...                         Narcissa...
White Oak...                      Ottawa...
Peoria...                         Cardin...
Hollow...                         Centrailia...
Pyramid Corners...                Centralia...
This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 278 and 324.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
